    <section>
      <h>imperative</h>
      <p><ul>
          <li><ul id="imperative">
              <li>independent <ul id="imp-ind">
                  <li>first person singular – <m>faigheam</m>!</li>
                  <li>second person singular – <m>faigh</m>!</li>
                  <li>first person plural – <m>faigheamaid</m>!</li>
                  <li>second person plural – <m>faighibh</m>!</li>
                  <li>third person – <m>faigheadh</m>!</li>
                  <li>passive – <m>faigh(t)ear</m>!</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>dependent <ul id="imp-dep">
                  <li>first person singular – na <m>faigheam</m>!</li>
                  <li>second person singular – na <m>faigh</m>!</li>
                  <li>first person plural – na <m>faigheamaid</m>!</li>
                  <li>second person plural – na <m>faighibh</m>!</li>
                  <li>third person – na <m>faigheadh</m>!</li>
                  <li>passive – na <m>faigh(t)ear</m>!</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </section>
    <p>Notes – <ol>
          <li>The past independent forms <g>fhuair</g> and <g>fhuaras</g> are pronounced as if they
            were spelled <g>thuair</g> and <g>thuaras</g>.</li>
          <li>The past dependent forms <g>do fhuair</g> and <g>do fhuaras</g> are pronounced as if
            they were spelled <g>duair</g> and <g>duaras</g>. They are commonly written as <g>d’
              fhuair</g> and <g>d’ fhuaras</g>.</li>
          <li>There is an alternative dialectal future / conditional stem – <g>gheobh-</g>.</li>
          <li>There is an alternative dialectal verbal noun – <g>faotainn</g>.</li>
        </ol>
    </p>
  </section>
  
